cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with neural network architecture for extracting features from high-resolution signals associated with 3D surface meshes. The paper also discusses the use of convolution on a surface, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also introduces a new convolutional operator, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and discusses its application in 3D semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
